<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-05T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-05T10:00:00-05:00" n="431" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d431">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">882.51/933: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                        Peace</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-05T16:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">May 5,
                                            1919, 4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                        May 5, 2.07 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>1990. Commission’s 1772, April 24, 7 p.m. Peretti informs us that in
                                conformity with our conversation with him instructions were issued
                                to Fardet, the new French Receiver in Liberia, to suspend his
                                departure from France, but that it has just been ascertained that he
                                left on April 8.</p>
                            <closer><hi rend="smallcaps">American Mission</hi></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>